Note: ============================================================================
Note: Canonical "is ..." Comparison Phrase Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Runa spells comparisons as natural-language phrases: "X is equal to Y",
"X is greater than Y", "X is less than or equal to Y", and their negations
"X is not ...". The lexer tokenises every word of the phrase separately
(TOKEN_IS, TOKEN_NOT, TOKEN_GREATER, TOKEN_LESS, TOKEN_THAN, TOKEN_EQUAL,
TOKEN_TO, TOKEN_OR), so the parser — not the lexer — assembles them into a
single comparison operator. The Pratt loop dispatches here whenever it sees
the leading "is" particle.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Consumes the "is" particle, an optional "not" (which inverts the relation),
then one of the comparison cores:
  - "equal to"                      -> EQUAL (400)        / not -> NOT_EQUAL (511)
  - "greater than"                  -> GREATER_THAN (513) / not -> LESS_EQUAL (514)
  - "greater than or equal to"      -> GREATER_EQUAL (515)/ not -> LESS_THAN (512)
  - "less than"                     -> LESS_THAN (512)    / not -> GREATER_EQUAL (515)
  - "less than or equal to"         -> LESS_EQUAL (514)   / not -> GREATER_THAN (513)
  - bare "is <value>" (no core)     -> EQUAL (400)        / not -> NOT_EQUAL (511)
The chosen token is exactly the canonical comparison token the HIR/MIR
binary-operator mapping (map_binary_operator_to_mir_opcode) recognises, so
the comparison lowers to the correct MIR_CMP opcode. The right operand is
parsed at one level tighter than comparison (PRECEDENCE_COMPARISON_LEVEL + 1)
so "a is greater than b plus c" groups as "a > (b + c)".
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
A handful of token reads/consumes plus one recursive operand parse. Cold
relative to the arithmetic-heavy inner expression loop.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Every particle is consumed via parser_expect_token / explicit type checks;
a malformed phrase (e.g. "greater" without "than") falls back to the bare
equality form rather than corrupting parser state, and the surrounding
statement parser surfaces the resulting token mismatch as a diagnostic.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "parse_is_comparison" takes parser as Integer, left as Integer returns Integer:
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If left is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Capture the "is" token position for the comparison AST node.
    Let is_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let op_line be proc token_get_line from Parser with is_token
    Let op_column be proc token_get_column from Parser with is_token

    Note: Consume "is".
    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

    Note: Optional "not" negation.
    Let is_negated be 0
    Let after_is be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let after_is_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with after_is
    If after_is_type is equal to TOKEN_NOT:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        Set is_negated to 1
        Set after_is to proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Set after_is_type to proc token_get_type from Parser with after_is
    End If

    Note: "is [not] within ..." delegates to the range-membership parser.
    If after_is_type is equal to TOKEN_WITHIN:
        Return proc parse_is_within_expression with parser, left, is_negated
    End If

    Let comparison_op be 0

    Note: "equal to" -> EQUAL / NOT_EQUAL.
    If after_is_type is equal to TOKEN_EQUAL:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_TO
        If is_negated is equal to 1:
            Set comparison_op to 511
        Otherwise:
            Set comparison_op to 400
        End If
    End If

    Note: "greater than [or equal to]" cluster.
    If after_is_type is equal to TOKEN_GREATER:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_THAN
        Let g_or be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Let g_or_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with g_or
        If g_or_type is equal to TOKEN_OR:
            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
            proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_EQUAL
            proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_TO
            If is_negated is equal to 1:
                Set comparison_op to 512
            Otherwise:
                Set comparison_op to 515
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If is_negated is equal to 1:
                Set comparison_op to 514
            Otherwise:
                Set comparison_op to 513
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: "less than [or equal to]" cluster.
    If after_is_type is equal to TOKEN_LESS:
        proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
        proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_THAN
        Let l_or be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Let l_or_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with l_or
        If l_or_type is equal to TOKEN_OR:
            proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
            proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_EQUAL
            proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_TO
            If is_negated is equal to 1:
                Set comparison_op to 513
            Otherwise:
                Set comparison_op to 514
            End If
        Otherwise:
            If is_negated is equal to 1:
                Set comparison_op to 515
            Otherwise:
                Set comparison_op to 512
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Bare "is <value>" / "is not <value>" shorthand for equality.
    If comparison_op is equal to 0:
        If is_negated is equal to 1:
            Set comparison_op to 511
        Otherwise:
            Set comparison_op to 400
        End If
    End If

    Note: Right operand binds tighter than comparison so arithmetic on the
    Note: right-hand side groups before the comparison applies.
    Let right be proc parse_expression_with_precedence with parser, PRECEDENCE_COMPARISON_LEVEL plus 1
    If right is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected expression after comparison operator", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Let comparison_node be proc build_binary_expression from ASTBuilder with comparison_op, left, right, op_line, op_column
    If comparison_node is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Failed to create comparison expression AST node", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Return comparison_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Binary Expression Parsing
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "parse_binary_expression" takes parser as Integer, left as Integer, operator as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a binary expression
    Note: .
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   parser - Pointer to ParserState
    Note:   left - Pointer to left operand AST node
    Note:   operator - Operator token type
    Note: .
    Note: Returns:
    Note:   Pointer to binary expression AST node
    Note:   Returns 0 on parsing error
    Note: .
    Note: Algorithm:
    Note: 1. Get operator precedence using Precedence.get_operator_precedence
    Note: 2. Consume operator token
    Note: 3. Parse right operand using parse_expression_with_precedence
    Note:    - Use precedence + 1 as min_precedence
    Note: 4. Create binary expression AST node using ASTBuilder.build_binary_expression
    Note: 5. Return binary expression AST node

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If left is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Get operator precedence
    Let precedence be proc get_operator_precedence from Precedence with operator

    Note: Capture the operator token position for the AST node before it is consumed.
    Let operator_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let op_line be proc token_get_line from Parser with operator_token
    Let op_column be proc token_get_column from Parser with operator_token

    Note: Special handling for "is within" compound operator (Language Additions v0.0.8.5)
    If operator is equal to TOKEN_IS:
        Note: Check if this is "is within" or "is not within"
        Let next_token be proc parser_peek_token from Parser with parser, 1
        If next_token is not equal to 0:
            Let next_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with next_token

            Note: Handle "is within lower to upper"
            If next_type is equal to TOKEN_WITHIN:
                Return proc parse_is_within_expression with parser, left, 0
            End If

            Note: Handle "is not within lower to upper"
            If next_type is equal to TOKEN_NOT:
                Let third_token be proc parser_peek_token from Parser with parser, 2
                If third_token is not equal to 0:
                    Let third_type be proc token_get_type from Parser with third_token
                    If third_type is equal to TOKEN_WITHIN:
                        Return proc parse_is_within_expression with parser, left, 1
                    End If
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Consume the operator token
    proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser

    Note: Multi-word arithmetic operators (runa_formal_grammar.md): the
    Note: multiplicative operators are spelled "multiplied by" / "divided by" /
    Note: "modulo by", which the lexer tokenises as the operator keyword
    Note: (TOKEN_MULTIPLIED 393 / TOKEN_DIVIDED 394 / TOKEN_MODULO 504) followed
    Note: by the particle "by" (TOKEN_BY 387). The operator token was consumed
    Note: above; consume the trailing "by" so the right-operand parse begins at
    Note: the real operand rather than failing on the particle (which otherwise
    Note: aborts the expression and silently drops the whole enclosing
    Note: statement/function).
    If operator is equal to 393:
        Let by_tok_mul be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        If by_tok_mul is not equal to 0:
            If proc token_get_type from Parser with by_tok_mul is equal to 387:
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If operator is equal to 394:
        Let by_tok_div be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        If by_tok_div is not equal to 0:
            If proc token_get_type from Parser with by_tok_div is equal to 387:
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
            End If
        End If
    End If
    If operator is equal to 504:
        Let by_tok_mod be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        If by_tok_mod is not equal to 0:
            If proc token_get_type from Parser with by_tok_mod is equal to 387:
                proc parser_consume_token from Parser with parser
            End If
        End If
    End If

    Note: Determine right precedence based on associativity
    Let assoc be proc get_operator_associativity from Precedence with operator
    Let right_precedence be precedence

    Note: For left-associative (assoc=0), use precedence + 1
    Note: For right-associative (assoc=1), use precedence
    If assoc is equal to 0:
        Set right_precedence to precedence plus 1
    End If

    Note: Parse right operand with appropriate precedence
    Let right be proc parse_expression_with_precedence with parser, right_precedence

    If right is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected expression after binary operator", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Build binary expression AST node
    Let binary_node be proc build_binary_expression from ASTBuilder with operator, left, right, op_line, op_column

    If binary_node is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Failed to create binary expression AST node", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Return binary_node
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Ternary Expression Parsing (v0.0.8.5)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "parse_ternary_expression" takes parser as Integer, condition as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Parse a ternary expression (condition ? true_value : false_value)
    Note: .
    Note: Parameters:
    Note:   parser - Pointer to ParserState
    Note:   condition - Pointer to condition expression AST node
    Note: .
    Note: Returns:
    Note:   Pointer to ternary expression AST node
    Note:   Returns 0 on parsing error
    Note: .
    Note: Algorithm:
    Note: 1. Expect and consume ? token
    Note: 2. Parse true value using parse_expression
    Note: 3. Expect and consume : token
    Note: 4. Parse false value using parse_expression
    Note: 5. Create ternary expression AST node using ASTBuilder.build_ternary_expression
    Note: 6. Return ternary expression AST node

    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    If condition is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Capture the ternary operator position for the AST node.
    Let ternary_token be proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
    Let ter_line be proc token_get_line from Parser with ternary_token
    Let ter_column be proc token_get_column from Parser with ternary_token

    Note: Expect and consume question mark
    Let result be proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_QUESTION_MARK
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse true branch expression
    Let true_expr be proc parse_expression with parser

    If true_expr is equal to 0:
        proc parser_report_error from Parser with parser, 2, proc create_from_literal from StringCore with "Expected expression after '?' in ternary operator", proc token_get_line from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser, proc token_get_column from Parser with proc parser_current_token from Parser with parser
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Expect and consume colon
    Set result to proc parser_expect_token from Parser with parser, TOKEN_COLON
    If result is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Parse false branch expression
    Let false_expr be proc parse_expression with parser

    If false_expr is equal to 0:
